      humorLevel: 'medium',
      content: `Gynecomastia—or "gyno"—is the development of breast tissue in men. It's more common than you think, and more fixable than you fear.

**What It Is:**
- Actual breast gland tissue (not just fat)
- Affects 30-70% of men at some point in life
- Can be one-sided or both
- Often includes puffy/protruding nipples

**What It's NOT:**
- Not always your fault
- Not always from steroids
- Not "just fat" (though fat makes it worse)
- Not something you have to live with

**Causes:**
| Cause | Mechanism |
|-------|-----------|
| Puberty | Hormone fluctuations (usually resolves) |
| Obesity | Aromatization of testosterone to estrogen |
| Medications | Some antidepressants, anti-ulcer, etc. |
| Steroids | Testosterone converts to estrogen |
| Low testosterone | Hormonal imbalance |
| Aging | Testosterone decline |
| Drugs/alcohol | Various mechanisms |

**The Honest Truth:**
Most gynecomastia won't resolve on its own in adults. If you have actual glandular tissue, surgery is often the only permanent fix.

**This Guide Covers:**
1. Determining if it's gyno or fat
2. Non-surgical interventions
3. Surgical options
4. Post-treatment maintenance`,
